00:23:49,931 --> 00:23:53,097
We have the matcha sponge,

261
00:23:53,301 --> 00:23:56,911
which will give you an earthy flavor because it's spring.

262
00:23:56,971 --> 00:24:00,941
The black represents Min Ki, and the white one is me.

263
00:24:01,951 --> 00:24:03,851
The flavor of those two sesame represents...

264
00:24:03,851 --> 00:24:07,321
transition from winter to spring,

265
00:24:07,721 --> 00:24:12,121
just like our initial awkwardness and newness.

266
00:24:12,191 --> 00:24:14,691
Like a refreshing fruit blossoming in spring,

267
00:24:14,761 --> 00:24:17,961
we wanted to express that refreshing feeling with the lemon curd.

268
00:24:20,331 --> 00:24:25,271
It's inspired by the notebook that Min Ki gave me.

269
00:24:25,341 --> 00:24:28,336
I want to read this to you.

270
00:24:28,963 --> 00:24:33,241
If someone gives you sesame oil in a simple bottle with no label,

271
00:24:33,307 --> 00:24:35,777
it means they truly love you.

272
00:24:37,851 --> 00:24:39,749
That gave me a deep impression.

273
00:24:39,802 --> 00:24:42,710
That's why I made a sesame-forward dessert.

274
00:24:43,452 --> 00:24:48,296
I wrote down things for her about Korean culture and history,

275
00:24:48,664 --> 00:24:51,316
And I think she was really inspired by it.

276
00:24:54,654 --> 00:24:56,424
Gosh.

277
00:24:56,531 --> 00:24:59,222
You can tell how much thought went into this.

278
00:24:59,915 --> 00:25:03,011
- Thank you. - No.

279
00:25:03,071 --> 00:25:05,911
Still trying to be her muse, I see.

280
00:25:08,551 --> 00:25:09,758
The lemon curd...

281
00:25:10,312 --> 00:25:13,404
is tricky to make properly. But this lemon curd...

282
00:25:15,806 --> 00:25:18,906
It has a fishy taste.

283
00:25:20,221 --> 00:25:24,161
Instead of cutting through all the nutty flavors,

284
00:25:24,161 --> 00:25:27,061
it came across as a bit unpleasant.

285
00:25:27,131 --> 00:25:31,601
- That part is a real shame. - I...

286
00:25:31,671 --> 00:25:33,141
had a similar thought.

287
00:25:33,141 --> 00:25:37,411
However, I thought the black sesame and another sesame...

288
00:25:37,411 --> 00:25:38,835
Both tasted wonderful.

289
00:25:39,017 --> 00:25:42,325
The meaning you were going for, and the way the two came together...

290
00:25:42,350 --> 00:25:46,760
I personally felt that excitement, like a blossoming spring.

291
00:25:49,691 --> 00:25:51,591
Great work, you two.

292
00:25:51,733 --> 00:25:56,633
Let's take a look at the dessert from Jan Yu and Im Sung Kyun's team.

293
00:26:08,471 --> 00:26:12,311
Our dessert describes autumn.

294
00:26:12,381 --> 00:26:15,251
Inside, we have a matcha custard.

295
00:26:15,311 --> 00:26:18,857
But I used the Korean ingredient, sikhye,

296
00:26:19,057 --> 00:26:21,191
to replace some of the milk.

297
00:26:21,851 --> 00:26:25,421
Because I didn't want a milky flavor.

298
00:26:25,791 --> 00:26:29,991
So I made a fresh one so that matcha taste can come through.

299
00:26:30,161 --> 00:26:35,331
As we are expressing autumn... You can see the small choux...

300
00:26:35,331 --> 00:26:40,471
resting on the big one. It represents the bond between us.

301
00:26:40,471 --> 00:26:45,811
It's very stable and it's a strengthened bond.

302
00:26:49,381 --> 00:26:54,551
First off, visually, it captures the essence of autumn.

303
00:26:54,621 --> 00:26:59,721
You did a wonderful job in design. It's very well-made.

304
00:26:59,825 --> 00:27:00,862
However,

305
00:27:01,361 --> 00:27:06,931
the balance of the components feels just a little bit off to me.

306
00:27:07,231 --> 00:27:10,043
One reason is the bitterness of the matcha.

307
00:27:10,136 --> 00:27:13,663
That bitterness really lingered on my palate.

308
00:27:14,171 --> 00:27:17,971
Personally, regarding the flavor, I found the strong matcha taste...

309
00:27:19,011 --> 00:27:22,711
to be a plus.

310
00:27:23,351 --> 00:27:24,881
These days, things like matcha lattes...

311
00:27:25,124 --> 00:27:27,694
are a massive global trend.

312
00:27:27,721 --> 00:27:32,261
I'd say it felt like drinking a very rich matcha latte.

313
00:27:35,461 --> 00:27:40,361
Let's taste the last team's dessert. Team Luvita and Lee Sae On.

314
00:27:43,871 --> 00:27:44,871
I chose winter.

315
00:27:47,241 --> 00:27:50,471
Because winter reminds me of warmth,

316
00:27:50,541 --> 00:27:54,681
familiarity, holiday, and comfort. Because yesterday,

317
00:27:54,741 --> 00:27:59,181
we went to the West Coast. It was really cold, really cold.

318
00:27:59,181 --> 00:28:01,081
I've never been to any beach.

319
00:28:01,791 --> 00:28:03,021
It's near the sea.

320
00:28:03,091 --> 00:28:05,291
- Yes. - So it's even worse.

321
00:28:05,361 --> 00:28:08,391
He's more laid back, chill, warm,

322
00:28:08,391 --> 00:28:11,191
and very comfortable to be with. That's why...

323
00:28:11,216 --> 00:28:12,769
I want to represent with this dessert.

324
00:28:13,801 --> 00:28:16,471
It's winter. It's like a holiday season.

325
00:28:16,531 --> 00:28:20,196
So I made this with some cinnamon, apple, and caramel.

326
00:28:20,601 --> 00:28:24,671
The taste is very familiar. When you eat it,

327
00:28:24,741 --> 00:28:27,841
it tastes like the holidays. It tastes like winter.

328
00:28:27,911 --> 00:28:32,021
The inside is whipped dulce doenjang ganache.

329
00:28:32,081 --> 00:28:33,821
Maybe someone at the table...

330
00:28:33,881 --> 00:28:37,251
might want to have a stronger taste of doenjang.

331
00:28:37,551 --> 00:28:40,107
So I made it on the side as an option...

332
00:28:40,132 --> 00:28:42,768
just in case you want to have a stronger doenjang flavor.

333
00:28:47,031 --> 00:28:50,301
I thought the overall balance...

334
00:28:51,361 --> 00:28:54,701
of flavors was excellent.

335
00:28:54,916 --> 00:28:59,486
The sweetness of the dessert, the texture of the choux...

336
00:28:59,511 --> 00:29:03,451
The caramelized apples were crisp, not mushy.

337
00:29:03,451 --> 00:29:06,581
So when it comes to the flavor, I have to say it was wonderful.

338
00:29:06,651 --> 00:29:10,744
I was disappointed by the design.

339
00:29:10,843 --> 00:29:16,113
I wondered how it would be nice if the design was more captivating.

340
00:29:17,331 --> 00:29:23,631
The cream had a nice body, which fit the winter theme.

341
00:29:23,701 --> 00:29:25,501
I liked that it had some body.

342
00:29:25,571 --> 00:29:29,471
If the cream had been lighter, I don't think it would have worked.

343
00:29:29,541 --> 00:29:33,811
Of all the creams Luvita has made, this one was the most impressive.

344
00:29:33,881 --> 00:29:35,011
I really enjoyed it.

345
00:29:37,811 --> 00:29:41,381
This one was certainly impressive.

346
00:29:42,351 --> 00:29:44,291
They should've added more butter to make it work.

347
00:29:48,261 --> 00:29:49,901
It's time to make our decision.

348
00:29:50,661 --> 00:29:52,461
I'll now announce the eliminated team.

349
00:30:00,041 --> 00:30:03,641
Luvita and Lee Sae On.

350
00:30:11,511 --> 00:30:12,821
The two of you...

351
00:30:14,881 --> 00:30:18,961
- The two of you have survived. - Gosh. It startled me.

352
00:30:21,161 --> 00:30:27,231
You get to continue on to the third round.

353
00:30:28,401 --> 00:30:30,301
Gosh, hold on. Thank you.

354
00:30:33,041 --> 00:30:34,041
Gosh.

355
00:30:34,943 --> 00:30:37,549
Team Jan Yu and Im Sung Kyun. And Team Jessica and Bae Min Ki.

356
00:30:37,730 --> 00:30:40,681
Please step forward.

357
00:30:40,977 --> 00:30:45,581
One of these teams will be moving on to the next round.

358
00:30:45,698 --> 00:30:48,233
So, which team will be moving on to Round Three?

359
00:30:48,787 --> 00:30:49,787
The team eliminated in Round Two...

360
00:30:53,476 --> 00:30:56,891
is Jan Yu and Im Sung Kyun.

361
00:30:57,884 --> 00:31:00,424
You two have been eliminated.

362
00:31:01,757 --> 00:31:02,797
Thank you.

363
00:31:10,733 --> 00:31:12,973
You have an aesthetic and you're clever.

364
00:31:13,196 --> 00:31:14,541
And you have great ideas.

365
00:31:14,611 --> 00:31:17,681
But where you're falling a little short is...

366
00:31:17,681 --> 00:31:21,851
that the balance of your main cream is just slightly off.

367
00:31:21,921 --> 00:31:24,651
This time, if only the matcha cream had been a bit sweeter,

368
00:31:24,721 --> 00:31:27,961
I think it would have been a truly outstanding flavor.

369
00:31:29,841 --> 00:31:34,681
Give a big hand to my partner because he really helped me a lot.

370
00:31:35,177 --> 00:31:39,647
So I really want to thank him, Sung Kyun.

371
00:31:41,501 --> 00:31:45,873
Jan Yu's desserts are number one in my mind.

372
00:31:46,637 --> 00:31:48,360
I'll always be rooting for her.

373
00:31:48,981 --> 00:31:52,221
I want to give her a round of applause for working so hard.

374
00:31:52,500 --> 00:31:53,451
You worked so hard.

375
00:32:02,991 --> 00:32:06,461
As we were covering the station, I was only looking at Jan Yu's face.

376
00:32:07,131 --> 00:32:08,963
I was just hoping she wouldn't cry.

377
00:32:09,871 --> 00:32:12,301
Why couldn't I have been more helpful?

378
00:32:16,471 --> 00:32:19,641
- I'm so tired. - Jan Yu. Oh, no.

379
00:32:28,951 --> 00:32:32,691
I felt even more sorry, and it hit me that it was over.

380
00:32:32,761 --> 00:32:38,091
I realized we weren't going to Singapore.

381
00:32:39,207 --> 00:32:41,737
Sung Kyun.

382
00:32:42,706 --> 00:32:45,346
Don't feel sorry about this...

383
00:32:45,371 --> 00:32:50,071
because you helped me a lot, and we already won Mission Two.

384
00:32:50,141 --> 00:32:54,341
I'm just so grateful that I got to work with you.

385
00:32:54,411 --> 00:32:58,111
The moments we spent together mean more to me...

386
00:32:58,774 --> 00:33:01,534
than winning this competition.

387
00:33:06,021 --> 00:33:09,561
Hey, don't ignore my texts just because you get busy.

388
00:33:09,631 --> 00:33:13,701
I'll reach out first, so let's definitely meet up again.

389
00:33:13,861 --> 00:33:16,501
Thank you for everything. Bye.

390
00:33:21,541 --> 00:33:24,071
First, K-SWEETHEART.

391
00:33:24,071 --> 00:33:25,511
- K-SWEETHEART. - Really?

392
00:33:25,581 --> 00:33:31,681
They had to create a K-dessert that embodies their Muses.

393
00:33:31,711 --> 00:33:34,781
- It's Some and Ssam. - Some and Ssam?

394
00:33:34,881 --> 00:33:35,921
Ssam?

395
00:33:35,921 --> 00:33:38,221
- Are you having fun? - No fun. Happy.

396
00:33:38,221 --> 00:33:40,991
- Happy. - You are a genius.

397
00:33:41,061 --> 00:33:42,961
I think you are a genius.

398
00:33:43,031 --> 00:33:45,781
Final Mission: You and Me in Season.

399
00:33:46,631 --> 00:33:48,601
Lin Lin and Cha Joo Wan's team.

400
00:33:48,601 --> 00:33:50,231
Jan Nichcha and Sung Seung Ha's team.

401
00:33:50,231 --> 00:33:52,101
And Jan Yu and Im Sung Kyun's team.

402
00:33:52,171 --> 00:33:54,371
Only two teams remain.

403
00:34:00,181 --> 00:34:03,111
I want to win this competition.

404
00:34:03,111 --> 00:34:05,721
We've come this far, so there's no reason we can't.

405
00:34:06,621 --> 00:34:07,621
Me and Sae On.

406
00:34:07,681 --> 00:34:10,651
We were so desperate to go to Singapore.

407
00:34:10,721 --> 00:34:14,421
I'm confident of my flavor profile.

408
00:34:14,491 --> 00:34:19,161
So my mindset is like, "Just do it."

409
00:34:19,231 --> 00:34:22,431
Jessica, we have to go to Singapore.

410
00:34:29,071 --> 00:34:34,241
For this third round, in addition to your last dessert,

411
00:34:34,441 --> 00:34:40,851
you'll need to plate the desserts you made in Rounds 1 and 2,

412
00:34:40,921 --> 00:34:44,451
and present them all as a single dessert course.

413
00:34:44,496 --> 00:34:46,866
How about you say something to each other?

414
00:34:46,891 --> 00:34:49,291
- Anything you'd like to say? - Sae On.

415
00:34:50,291 --> 00:34:53,361
Your dessert looks a little gloomy. We're the ones who are going to win.

416
00:34:55,861 --> 00:34:56,861
Hey.

417
00:34:57,831 --> 00:35:03,488
Winners keep on winning. Since we won the first mission,

418
00:35:04,171 --> 00:35:08,241
we'll be the ones taking the final prize.

419
00:35:10,311 --> 00:35:12,121
Alright, very good.

420
00:35:12,181 --> 00:35:16,921
I'm sure the two teams already have a game plan.

421
00:35:17,421 --> 00:35:20,121
But...

422
00:35:21,591 --> 00:35:25,561
this final round has a hidden ingredient.

423
00:35:25,763 --> 00:35:29,601
- There is a hidden ingredient. - My gosh.

424
00:35:30,601 --> 00:35:31,901
A hidden mission.

425
00:35:33,334 --> 00:35:36,581
What is it? What's this situation?

426
00:35:37,448 --> 00:35:38,715
Something is changed?

427
00:35:40,211 --> 00:35:41,881
Gosh!

428
00:35:43,027 --> 00:35:45,827
- Gosh. - Gosh.

429
00:35:47,051 --> 00:35:49,921
- Gosh. - Gosh.

430
00:35:51,851 --> 00:35:54,091
The hidden ingredient is strawberries.

431
00:35:54,254 --> 00:35:56,054
- Strawberry. - Strawberry.

432
00:35:57,207 --> 00:35:59,947
Strawberries that represent winter and spring in Korea.

433
00:36:01,431 --> 00:36:06,801
You must use these strawberries to complete your dessert spread.

434
00:36:07,123 --> 00:36:08,116
Starting now,

435
00:36:08,141 --> 00:36:10,211
you may begin your discussion.

436
00:36:14,811 --> 00:36:17,951
What happened? I really have mixed feelings.

437
00:36:19,221 --> 00:36:24,221
My gosh. We're lucky.

438
00:36:27,521 --> 00:36:29,131
The moment they said there was a hidden ingredient,

439
00:36:29,131 --> 00:36:32,401
and we should use that...

440
00:36:33,461 --> 00:36:36,031
Gosh, it's strawberry. It's like destiny.

441
00:36:36,101 --> 00:36:38,301
I have strawberries in my recipes.

442
00:36:43,644 --> 00:36:46,562
I think I just thought to myself, "Wait, what?"

443
00:36:46,881 --> 00:36:51,984
I think I was just trying to hide how happy I was.

444
00:37:02,061 --> 00:37:03,291
It's good?

445
00:37:05,901 --> 00:37:08,531
- So big. - I know.

446
00:37:08,601 --> 00:37:12,031
It's already a good product. So we just need to enhance...

447
00:37:12,101 --> 00:37:13,901
the strawberry, right?

448
00:37:17,771 --> 00:37:19,081
Really good?

449
00:37:21,541 --> 00:37:24,411
- And it's juicy. - Right. Good.

450
00:37:24,811 --> 00:37:27,681
It's really sweet. Sweet. So sweet.

451
00:37:27,751 --> 00:37:30,451
- Are you ready? - I'm ready.

452
00:37:30,761 --> 00:37:33,061
We're lucky. We can do it.

453
00:37:34,961 --> 00:37:38,691
- Alright, are both teams ready? - Yes.

454
00:37:39,701 --> 00:37:41,901
Let's begin the final round.

455
00:37:41,961 --> 00:37:45,301
Once again, you have two hours.

456
00:37:45,371 --> 00:37:49,041
Final Mission, You and Me in Season, Round Three.

457
00:37:50,271 --> 00:37:54,441
Take a bite! Your time starts now.

458
00:37:54,511 --> 00:37:55,581
Take a bite.

459
00:37:56,581 --> 00:37:58,311
Take a bite.

460
00:38:02,591 --> 00:38:03,721
Eighty, eighty.

461
00:38:09,461 --> 00:38:12,614
And for the spring theme, I decided to make cakes for him...

462
00:38:12,954 --> 00:38:16,604
because this could be our last time working together.

463
00:38:16,801 --> 00:38:19,271
But I want to make it a whole cake, like a birthday cake.

464
00:38:19,341 --> 00:38:20,691
I think it's more meaningful...

465
00:38:20,716 --> 00:38:23,216
when you actually make them from scratch.

466
00:38:24,571 --> 00:38:28,781
Luvita is going to make a whole cake for this final round.

467
00:38:29,251 --> 00:38:31,851
She whipped the whole eggs together.

468
00:38:31,851 --> 00:38:35,521
- It would be heavy, but also soft. - Right, it will be moist genoise.

469
00:38:35,830 --> 00:38:38,030
She must have various kinds of experience.

470
00:38:40,094 --> 00:38:44,364
Cut the tea inside all the powder.

471
00:38:47,114 --> 00:38:50,416
I think she's going to make Earl Grey cake.

472
00:38:50,993 --> 00:38:54,171
Earl Grey goes well with strawberries.

473
00:38:54,195 --> 00:38:57,149
I heard she was saying that.

474
00:38:57,207 --> 00:39:01,875
If you make the cake sheet in yellow color without using tea,

475
00:39:01,900 --> 00:39:04,201
you can see the cake surface...

476
00:39:04,226 --> 00:39:06,350
- you're familiar with. - Right.

477
00:39:06,376 --> 00:39:09,821
I don't know if it looks good...

478
00:39:10,256 --> 00:39:12,791
when they make the sheet by putting the Earl Grey.

479
00:39:31,811 --> 00:39:34,611
Inspired by Obangsaek, I made...

480
00:39:34,681 --> 00:39:37,251
each dessert with each color.

481
00:39:37,781 --> 00:39:41,321
Her dessert is a whole cake,

482
00:39:41,381 --> 00:39:43,891
and I'm a plated one.

483
00:39:44,021 --> 00:39:47,921
That's my style, plated desserts.

484
00:39:48,721 --> 00:39:53,631
I'll just have fun. But in the back of my head,

485
00:39:53,656 --> 00:39:57,156
I still want to win this competition.

486
00:40:04,094 --> 00:40:06,321
We have eggs.

487
00:40:07,075 --> 00:40:10,286
Egg, sugar, vanilla. Here.

488
00:40:10,311 --> 00:40:12,281
Egg, sugar, vanilla.

489
00:40:15,251 --> 00:40:18,151
- Weigh out your yogurt and oil. - Yogurt and oil.

490
00:40:20,921 --> 00:40:21,991
Okay.

491
00:40:23,361 --> 00:40:28,261
- Targrini? What is this? Targrini? - The tea.

492
00:40:29,637 --> 00:40:30,867
This?

493
00:40:34,841 --> 00:40:36,611
Open. Open the tea bag.

494
00:40:47,551 --> 00:40:53,161
They're going to pipe it into a quenelle mold and bake it.

495
00:40:53,520 --> 00:40:56,736
Jessica's really good at making fine dining desserts,

496
00:40:56,761 --> 00:41:01,301
so I'm looking forward to seeing what fancy dessert she makes.

497
00:41:29,021 --> 00:41:30,031
Wanna try?

498
00:41:30,031 --> 00:41:31,731
- Should I try it? - Yes, go ahead.

499
00:41:31,791 --> 00:41:33,301
- This piece? - Yes.

500
00:41:37,071 --> 00:41:38,631
I like the flavor.

501
00:41:38,701 --> 00:41:40,641
- You like it? - I do.

502
00:41:44,211 --> 00:41:45,241
You like it?

503
00:41:45,311 --> 00:41:46,411
Good.

504
00:41:57,391 --> 00:41:58,821
- Taste? - You want to taste?

505
00:42:00,591 --> 00:42:03,231
Gosh! Hey.

506
00:42:06,001 --> 00:42:08,831
The sponge cake rises as it bakes,

507
00:42:08,901 --> 00:42:12,101
so they'll cut that part off and only use the rest.

508
00:42:21,181 --> 00:42:25,081
Round Three is already halfway over.

509
00:42:26,081 --> 00:42:29,523
Sae On? Strawberry is already measured.

510
00:42:30,226 --> 00:42:33,396
Sugar, glucose. Okay?

511
00:42:37,461 --> 00:42:39,261
Gosh!

512
00:42:41,031 --> 00:42:44,531
- What should I do? - You put all the strawberries.

513
00:42:44,707 --> 00:42:46,077
Strawberry?

514
00:42:46,240 --> 00:42:48,500
